Field Detail

HTTP_METHOD

static final java.lang.String HTTP_METHOD
The name of the property in HTTP Exchanges that holds the HTTP method. The value of the property will be the string value if the method name, i.e. "GET", "PUT", "POST", "HEAD", "OPTIONS", "DELETE", "TRACE" or "CONNECT".

PROTOCOL_HEADERS

static final java.lang.String PROTOCOL_HEADERS
The NormalizedMessage property that holds the protocol headers. As defined in the spec, the value of the property is a Map but the Map values are protocol-dependant. In the case of SOAP the values are the DosumentFragment containing the SOAP header. See Final Release Spec 1.0 page 40. NB: Must match same named member of com.soa.jbi.messaging.MessageProperties. Duplicated here so as to avoid creating a dependency on any of the product bundles

See Also:
Constant Field Values

APPLICATION_SUBJECTS

static final java.lang.String APPLICATION_SUBJECTS
The set of subjects provided by the calling application in two situations:
  1. When running in Delegate mode.
  2. When the Agent subjects need to come from sources external to the message headers and payload.
Type should be Map
